            <div class="about-content">
                <h3>Our Vision</h3>
                <p>Our vision is to ensure every citizen has access to essential food items and commodities through a robust and inclusive ration shop system. We aim to create a society where no individual goes hungry, regardless of economic status or geographic location. By modernizing and expanding our network of ration shops, we envision a future where food security is a fundamental right upheld with dignity and efficiency.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="about-section as2">
            <div class="about-content">
                <h3>Our Mission</h3>
                <p>Our mission is to efficiently distribute subsidized food grains and essential commodities to eligible beneficiaries through a network of well-managed and technology-driven ration shops. We are committed to maintaining transparency, accountability, and fairness in the distribution process. Our mission extends beyond mere distribution; we strive to educate and empower communities on nutrition, health, and sustainable consumption practices to promote overall well-being.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="about-image">
                <img src="Images/mission.jpg" alt="Mission Image">
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="about-section">
            
            <div class="about-image">
                <img src="Images/approach.jpeg.jpg" alt="Vision Image">
            </div>

            <div class="about-content">
                <h3>Our Approach</h3>
                <p>Our approach revolves around leveraging technology to streamline operations and enhance service delivery in ration shops. We prioritize the digitalization of beneficiary records, real-time inventory management, and transparent distribution processes to minimize leakage and ensure timely access to ration supplies. Additionally, we foster partnerships with local communities, NGOs, and government agencies to address specific nutritional needs and promote community participation in the management and improvement of ration shop services.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
